    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-08T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-08T20:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/759: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-08T22:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 8, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 8—7:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1400. Referring to my telephone conversation this afternoon with the Under
                    Secretary and my telegram number 1395, December 8, noon.<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d59fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Following is text of reply received from Foreign Office today: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Ministry of Foreign Relations acknowledges the receipt of the <hi
                                rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> presented by the Embassy of the
                            United States of America under date of yesterday, by which, in making
                            known the acts of aggression of which the territory of the United States
                            has been the object on the part of the armed forces of Japan, it
                            requests, for the confidential information of its Government, an
                            expression of the views of the Argentine Government, in the light of
                            these circumstances and of the inter-American agreements in force.</p>
                        <p>In this connection the Ministry of Foreign Relations informs the Embassy
                            of the United States that the Argentine Government takes note of the
                            aggression committed against the integrity and the sovereignty of that
                            country, and that it is disposed to adapt its conduct to the situation
                            of reciprocal assistance and defensive cooperation providing [<hi
                                rend="italic">provided</hi>] for by Declaration XV of Habana,<note
                                n="11" xml:id="d59fn2">Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                                    >Bulletin</hi>, August 24, 1940, p. 136.</note> of which this
                            Government is a signatory.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am informed that the Foreign Office intends to make public the foregoing
                    statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
